<heading id="D09F8195FFD0D648FE8CFD27FD4AFD79" bold="true" box="[264,690,724,750]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C684D7AFFD0D648FE8CFD27FD4AFD79" authority="Ganglbauer" authorityName="Ganglbauer" box="[264,690,724,750]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Cephennium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallicum">
<emphasis id="B91CEAEBFFD0D648FE8CFD27FD4AFD79" bold="true" box="[264,690,724,750]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B91CEAEBFFD0D648FE8CFD27FDEEFD79" bold="true" box="[264,534,724,750]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cephennium gallicum</emphasis>
Ganglbauer
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD736F9FFD0D648FE8CFCECFE8DFBEE" blockId="5.[264,1323,799,1145]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
On five occasions (
<date id="FFD61039FFD0D648FE75FCECFD72FCAE" box="[497,650,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2001-07-07">
July 
<number id="3DA024DEFFD0D648FDAAFCECFD72FCAE" box="[558,650,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="7.2001">7, 2001</number>
</date>
, 
<date id="FFD61039FFD0D648FD1EFCECFCBDFCAE" box="[666,837,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2002-05-11">
May 
<number id="3DA024DEFFD0D648FD5DFCECFCBDFCAE" box="[729,837,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="11.2002">11, 2002</number>
</date>
, 
<date id="FFD61039FFD0D648FCD7FCECFC08FCAE" box="[851,1008,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2002-06-09">
June 
<number id="3DA024DEFFD0D648FC16FCECFC08FCAE" box="[914,1008,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="9.2002">9, 2002</number>
</date>
, 
<date id="FFD61039FFD0D648FC7AFCECFB09FCAE" box="[1022,1265,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2002-09-22">
September 
<number id="3DA024DEFFD0D648FB02FCECFB09FCAE" box="[1158,1265,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="22.2002">22, 2002</number>
</date>
, and 
<date id="FFD61039FFD0D648FE8CFCB4FE36FCF6" box="[264,462,839,865]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2004-10-09">
October 
<number id="3DA024DEFFD0D648FEF5FCB4FE36FCF6" box="[369,462,839,865]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="9.2004">9, 2004</number>
</date>
) six specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C684D7AFFD0D648FD33FCB4FBA8FCF6" authority="Ganglbauer" authorityName="Ganglbauer" box="[695,1104,839,865]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Cephennium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallicum">
<emphasis id="B91CEAEBFFD0D648FD33FCB4FC44FCF7" box="[695,956,839,864]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cephennium gallicum</emphasis>
Ganglbauer
</taxonomicName>
were collected in Point Pleasant Park. Five specimens were collected under the bark of branches or limbs of recently fallen or damaged white pine. The sixth specimen was collected while sweep netting through heath vegetation in a small sphagnum bog. Additionally, Peter Hammond collected four specimens in the Park in July, 
<number id="3DA024DEFFD0D648FD7AFC14FCC1FB96" box="[766,825,999,1025]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1988.0">1988</number>
(NHM). These records represent the first report of this species in North American (
<figureCitation id="13532A7CFFD0D648FD72FBFCFC9FFBBE" box="[758,871,1039,1065]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[264,368,1690,1714]" captionTargetBox="[335,1234,1225,1682]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[320,1256,1222,1683]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3: Cephennium gallicum Ganglbauer, Point Pleasant Park, Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada. Dorsal habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169605/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Figures 
<number id="3DA024DEFFD0D648FCDCFBFCFC9FFBBE" box="[856,871,1039,1065]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="13532A7CFFD0D648FC25FBFCFC4BFBBE" box="[929,947,1039,1065]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[264,368,1375,1399]" captionTargetBox="[411,1176,797,1361]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[344,1200,788,1367]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4: Cephennium gallicum Ganglbauer, Point Pleasant Park, Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada. Lateral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169606/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<number id="3DA024DEFFD0D648FC25FBFCFC4BFBBE" box="[929,947,1039,1065]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C684D7AFFD0D648FC50FBFCFB2EFBBF" box="[980,1238,1039,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Cephennium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallicum">
<emphasis id="B91CEAEBFFD0D648FC50FBFCFB2EFBBF" box="[980,1238,1039,1064]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cephennium gallicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also the only species of Palearctic scydmaenid known to have become established in North 
<taxonomicName id="4C684D7AFFD0D648FE8CFBACFE89FBEE" box="[264,369,1119,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="America" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<collectingCountry id="F37F7669FFD0D648FE8CFBACFE89FBEE" box="[264,369,1119,1145]" name="United States of America" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">America</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF176671FFD0D648FE8CF969FE52F943" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169605/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" targetBox="[335,1234,1225,1682]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BD736F9FFD0D648FE8CF969FE52F943" blockId="5.[264,1323,1690,1748]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
